---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie policy — book·lore" description="What cookies and storage book·lore uses.">
  <section class="spine page">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">book·lore</a> / <a href="/legal/">colophon</a> / cookies</p>
      <h1>Cookie policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <p>book·lore uses the smallest set of cookies and storage we can get away with.</p>

      <h2>What we set</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Reading ribbon</strong> — <code>localStorage</code> key
          <code>bookLore:&lt;slug&gt;:para</code> remembers the last paragraph you were on
          per book. No tracking; never leaves your device.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Auth session</strong> — when you sign in, Firebase Authentication sets
          cookies on <code>auth.oriz.in</code> so you stay logged in across every
          <code>*.oriz.in</code> site (book·lore included). These are first-party and
          essential.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Email link sign-in</strong> — <code>localStorage</code> key
          <code>oriz:emailForSignIn</code> holds your email between requesting and
          completing the sign-in link.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third parties</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare</strong> may set anti-abuse cookies (Turnstile, bot
          management). These are essential for site availability.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Opting out</h2>
      <p>
        Clear localStorage and cookies for <code>book-lore.oriz.in</code> and
        <code>auth.oriz.in</code> from your browser's site-data settings. The reading
        ribbon and auth will reset to defaults.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
